 ### Proof
 Let $\angle DBE = \alpha$ and $\angle DBC = \beta$. Then $\angle CBE = \alpha - \beta$ and $\angle ABE = \alpha + \beta$, so $\tan(\alpha - \beta)\tan(\alpha + \beta) = \tan^2 \alpha$.
